# UI — Gensyn Design System

This project uses the Gensyn design system. Follow it for all user-facing UI.

## Source

- Package path: `packages/gensyn-design-system/` (or copy from design-system repo)
- Style guide: https://YOUR_ORG.github.io/gensyn-design-system/
- Tokens: `tokens/colors.json`, `tokens/typography.json`

## CSS (required)

```css
@import './packages/gensyn-design-system/css/gensyn-tokens.css';
@import './packages/gensyn-design-system/css/gensyn-components.css';
```

Apply `class="gensyn-page"` on `<body>` (or root layout).

## Rules

- Font: Inter only (`var(--gensyn-font)`)
- Page background: `var(--gensyn-bg-gradient)` — do not use flat white pages
- Primary brand: `var(--gensyn-navy)` — headings, primary buttons, focus states
- Accent: `var(--gensyn-purple)` — section labels, footer links
- Content surfaces: `.gensyn-card` (white, 16px radius, soft shadow)
- Do not invent new hex colours; use CSS variables from `gensyn-tokens.css`
- Do not copy product logic from gensyn-diagnostic — only visual patterns

## Components

Prefer existing classes: `.gensyn-btn-primary`, `.gensyn-input`, `.gensyn-option`, `.gensyn-progress`, `.gensyn-badge`, `.gensyn-h1`, `.gensyn-subtitle`

Logo: `assets/gensyn-logo.svg` with `.gensyn-logo` or `.gensyn-logo--intake`

## When building new screens

1. Read `packages/gensyn-design-system/README.md`
2. Match layout: centered container, white card on lavender gradient
3. Ask before introducing new UI libraries that override these tokens
